org.jamesframework.core.search.listeners

Class EmptySearchListener<SolutionType extends Solution>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jamesframework.core.search.listeners.EmptySearchListener<SolutionType>
  • Type Parameters:
    SolutionType - solution type, required to extend Solution
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    SearchListener<SolutionType>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    EmptyLocalSearchListener

    public class EmptySearchListener<SolutionType extends Solution>
extends Object
implements SearchListener<SolutionType>
    An empty search listener contains empty implementations of all methods in SearchListener, acting as an easy entry point for custom search listeners which desire to listen only to a subset of events fired by a search, by overriding the corresponding empty implementation.
    Author:
    Herman De Beukelaer
